<subSubSection id="0A88F2D1FF9AFF94FF3DFE33FD82E0C1" box="[151,564,402,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph id="422DA15AFF9AFF94FF3DFE33FD82E0C1" blockId="15.[151,564,368,427]" box="[151,564,402,427]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FF3DFE33FE8CE0C1" box="[151,314,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–58" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1798,1821]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,195,1782]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[162,1425,195,1782]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 53–58. Left male palps in prolateral, dorsal, and retrolateral views. 53–55. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 56–58. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). Abbreviations: a, ‘appendix’ (main bulbal process); b, genital bulb; c, coxa; e, embolus; f, femur; p, procursus; ta, tarsus; ti, tibia; tr, trochanter. Scale lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625048/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figures 56–58</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FEECFE33FE39E0C1" box="[326,399,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–72" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1640,1663]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,194,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1619]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 65–72. Left procursi in retrolateral (upper row) and dorsal views. 65–66. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 67–68. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049); arrows point at subdistal dorsal process, asterisks mark prolateral processes. 69–70. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 71–72. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). At different scales." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625052/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">67–68</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FE30FE33FE54E0C1" box="[410,482,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 73–78" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,412,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,409,1858]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 73–78. Left genital bulbs in prolateral, dorsal, and retrolateral views. 73–75. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039); asterisks mark small sclerotized process close to proximal bulbal sclerite (Fig. 73) and distinctive conical projection (Fig. 74); arrow points at distinctive retrolateral membrane. 76–78. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). Abbreviations: a, ‘appendix’ (main bulbal process); b, genital bulb; e, embolus; pbs, proximal bulbal sclerite. Scales lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625054/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">76–78</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FE44FE33FDBAE0C1" box="[494,524,402,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–88" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1360,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,193,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1339]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 85–88. Epigyna in ventral views, all at same scale. 85. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 86. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 87. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 88. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Abbreviations: ep, epigynal plate; k, ‘knob’ (median epigynal process); pep, pre-epigynal plate. Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625058/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">86</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FDB2FE32FD82E0C1" box="[536,564,403,427]" captionStart="FIGURES 89–92" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1940,1963]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,916,1920]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,916,1920]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 89–92. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, all at same scale. 89. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 90. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 91. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 92. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625060/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">90</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0A88F2D1FF9AFF94FF3DFE7BFE93E3A1" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="422DA15AFF9AFF94FF3DFE7BFE93E3A1" blockId="15.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FF3DFE7BFEBCE099" bold="true" box="[151,266,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males are easily distinguished from other species in 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FCD3FE7BFC59E099" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[889,1007,474,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FCD3FE7BFC59E099" box="[889,1007,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by shape of genital bulb (
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FAC0FE7BFF54E37D" captionStart="FIGURES 73–78" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,412,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,409,1858]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 73–78. Left genital bulbs in prolateral, dorsal, and retrolateral views. 73–75. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039); asterisks mark small sclerotized process close to proximal bulbal sclerite (Fig. 73) and distinctive conical projection (Fig. 74); arrow points at distinctive retrolateral membrane. 76–78. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). Abbreviations: a, ‘appendix’ (main bulbal process); b, genital bulb; e, embolus; pbs, proximal bulbal sclerite. Scales lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625054/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 76–78</figureCitation>
): distinctive main bulbal process (‘appendix’), i.e. large sclerotized process without retrolateral membrane and retrolateral conical projection (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FD64FD85FCD4E351" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[718,866,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FD64FD85FCD4E351" box="[718,866,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), narrower in dorsal view than in 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FB59FD85FA22E351" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[1267,1428,548,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puranappui">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FB59FD85FA22E351" box="[1267,1428,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. puranappui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; without prolateral process (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FDCBFDE6FD17E334" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[609,673,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FDCBFDE6FD17E334" box="[609,673,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FC3FFDE6FC60E334" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[917,982,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FC3FFDE6FC60E334" box="[917,982,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by shape of procursus (
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FABCFDE7FA2EE335" box="[1302,1432,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–72" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1640,1663]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,194,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1619]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 65–72. Left procursi in retrolateral (upper row) and dorsal views. 65–66. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 67–68. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049); arrows point at subdistal dorsal process, asterisks mark prolateral processes. 69–70. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 71–72. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). At different scales." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625052/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 67–68</figureCitation>
; narrower and with subdistal dorsal process). Females are distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FBB9FDCDFB11E3E9" authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[1043,1191,618,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FBB9FDCDFB11E3E9" box="[1043,1191,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FB4EFDCDFA9EE3E9" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[1252,1320,620,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FB4EFDCDFA9EE3E9" box="[1252,1320,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by larger posterior excavation of pre-epigynal plate (
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FDD5FD2FFD65E3CD" box="[639,723,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–88" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1360,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,193,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1339]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 85–88. Epigyna in ventral views, all at same scale. 85. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 86. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 87. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 88. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Abbreviations: ep, epigynal plate; k, ‘knob’ (median epigynal process); pep, pre-epigynal plate. Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625058/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FC8DFD2EFC70E3CC" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[807,966,655,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puranappui">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FC8DFD2EFC70E3CC" box="[807,966,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. puranappui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by narrower pre-epigynal plate (compare 
<figureCitation id="DAA9BDDFFF9AFF94FF3DFD13FEAFE3A1" box="[151,281,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–88" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1360,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,193,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1339]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 85–88. Epigyna in ventral views, all at same scale. 85. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 86. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 87. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 88. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Abbreviations: ep, epigynal plate; k, ‘knob’ (median epigynal process); pep, pre-epigynal plate. Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625058/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 86–87</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0A88F2D1FF9AFF94FF6DFD77FCC5E279" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="422DA15AFF9AFF94FF6DFD77FCC5E279" blockId="15.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FF6DFD77FEF0E385" bold="true" box="[199,326,726,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is derived from the Pāli word 
<taxonomicName id="8592DAD9FF9AFF94FC0CFD76FC52E384" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[934,996,727,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metta">
<emphasis id="70E67D48FF9AFF94FC0CFD76FC52E384" box="[934,996,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">mettā</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of the four Buddhist virtues or brahmavihāras (active good will towards all); noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
